# Line-ending policy.
#
# This repo is developed cross-platform with core.autocrlf often left on. A
# number of shell scripts are executed *inside Linux* — the qemu-docker
# entrypoint runs via its `#!/usr/bin/env bash` shebang, and the macho/wine
# helpers run via `/bin/sh <script>`. A CRLF shebang makes the kernel look for
# `bash\r` (exit 127), and `set -e\r` / quoted args break under sh. So force
# LF on anything that must be Unix-executable, regardless of host checkout.
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.bash  text eol=lf

# Docker build-context files are consumed by the Linux image builder.
Dockerfile      text eol=lf
*.dockerfile    text eol=lf
